properties.NAME: Memorial Park
properties.Short_Desc: One of the older parks in the City situated near Old Pasadena. The park is characterized by a number of monuments, a large bandshell with seating capacity for 400, picnic facilities, benches, a large open grass area, restrooms and drinking fountains.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 5.3 acres.

properties.NAME: Central Park
properties.Short_Desc: This near downtown facility includes picnic tables, a rose garden, children’s playground area, benches, restrooms and drinking fountains.
properties.Desc1: Located in the City's Central District. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 9.2 acres.

properties.NAME: Singer Park
properties.Short_Desc: Small neighborhood park with open grass areas containing many well-established trees and rose beds. Other facilities include a children’s play area, picnic tables, benches, restrooms and a drinking fountain.
properties.Desc1: Located near the corner of California Boulevard and St. John Avenue. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 2.9 acres.

properties.NAME: Allendale Park
properties.Short_Desc: Major park attractions include one softball diamond with lights and bleachers (300 spectator capacity), one lighted multi-purpose field suitable for youth soccer and one tennis court with lights.
properties.Desc1: Located across from Blair High School and adjacent to Allendale Elementary, the hours of park operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 2.9 acres.

properties.NAME: Grant Park
properties.Short_Desc: This neighborhood park is ideally situated for use by downtown residents. Park facilities include two lighted tennis courts, half-basketball courts, and one softball diamond.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 2.5 acres.

properties.NAME: Hamilton Park
properties.Short_Desc: Large community park with three softball diamonds (two with seating capacity for 400), two lighted tennis courts, basketball court, paved volleyball court and a large multi-purpose field for flag football and soccer.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 6.4 acres.

properties.NAME: Jefferson Park
properties.Short_Desc: Park amenities include one lighted softball diamond (seating for 150 spectators), a small open field, lighted basketball court, a play areas, picnic tables, benches, restrooms and drinking fountains.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 4.4 acres.

properties.NAME: McDonald Park
properties.Short_Desc: Small neighborhood park offering one basketball court, a sand volleyball court, a two-sided handball court, one softball diamond, an open grass area, several picnic facilities and benches, restrooms, playground equipment and drinking fountains.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 4.8 acres.

properties.NAME: Washington Park
properties.Short_Desc: Large well-established neighborhood park offering two separate picnic areas, a small parking lot, two lighted tennis courts, one lighted basketball court, two one-wall handball courts, and one small softball diamond.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 5.5 acres.

properties.NAME: La Pintoresca Park
properties.Short_Desc: Well established Neighborhood Park with large trees and open grass area. The La Pintoresca Library and La Pintoresca Teen Education Center are also situated on site.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 2.9 acres.

properties.NAME: Brenner Park
properties.Short_Desc: A neighborhood park with a softball diamond for day use with bleacher seating for 72 spectators, a lighted tennis court, a lighted basketball court, a small open play area, a tot lot, picnic tables (some with canopies), restrooms and drinking fountains.
properties.Desc1: Located on the corner of Mountain Street and Barthe Drive. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 1.7 acres.

properties.NAME: San Rafael Park
properties.Short_Desc: Small neighborhood park offering benches, a small grass area, playground equipment, picnic facilities and a drinking fountain.
properties.Desc1: Located near the corner of Colorado Boulevard and Melrose Avenue. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 0.90 acres.

properties.NAME: Robinson Park
properties.Short_Desc: This park in NW Pasadena offers two lighted basketball courts, swimming pool, lighted synthetic turf sports fields with a football field and two baseball diamonds, picnic area, small open grass area, playground equipment, two parking lots and restrooms.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 7.0 acres.

properties.NAME: Villa Parke
properties.Short_Desc: This park is located near the downtown district. Park area includes a lighted softball diamond with bleachers, a lighted synthetic turf soccer field, a multi-purpose field, two basketball courts, and a swimming pool.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 8.1 acres.

properties.NAME: Lower Arroyo Park
properties.Short_Desc: This natural preserve area is used for activities which require an outdoor, rustic-type setting. Recreation activities available include one archery range, one bridle path, several cross-country trails, a lighted casting pool, a parking lot and benches.
properties.Desc1: Located west of Arroyo Boulevard stretching from the Holly Street Bridge to Pasadena’s southern City limits. Hours of operation are 6:00am to sundown. The size of the park is over 70 acres.

properties.NAME: Gwinn Park
properties.Short_Desc: Neighborhood Park situated on almost three acres of open grass area dotted with numerous young trees, across the street from Sunnyslope Park. Amenities include a picnic table and a drinking fountain.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 2.7 acres.

properties.NAME: Victory Park
properties.Short_Desc: Park area includes a large children’s play area, three lighted softball diamonds with bleachers, one lighted baseball diamond, one lighted multi-purpose suitable for soccer or flag football, and a sand volleyball court.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 24.6 acres.

properties.NAME: Sunnyslope Park
properties.Short_Desc: This neighborhood park across the street from Gwinn Park provides a children’s play area, picnic tables, drinking fountains and an open grass area.
properties.Desc1: Located at 3005 East Orange Grove Boulevard (near Sunnyslope Avenue). Hours of operation are from 6:00am to 10:00pm. The size of the park is 1.88 acres.

properties.NAME: Vina Vieja Park
properties.Short_Desc: This park provides a large picnic shelter, three additional picnic areas; and a dog park divided into two sections for large dogs and small dogs.
properties.Desc1: Located near Eaton Sunnyslope Park. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 7.5 acres.

properties.NAME: Brookside Park
properties.Short_Desc: Pasadena’s largest fully maintained park facility with an extensive list of park amenities and parking facilities available. The Rose Bowl Aquatic Center and KidSpace Children's Museum are located within the park grounds.
properties.Desc1: Located just south of the Rose Bowl. Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 61.1 acres.

properties.NAME: Defenders Parkway
properties.Short_Desc: This small neighborhood park on the southwest corner provides a small, open grassy area with some trees and shrubbery and a drinking fountain.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 1.8 acres.

properties.NAME: Hahamongna Watershed Park
properties.Short_Desc: This park in the northern section of the Arroyo Seco extends from Devil’s Gate Dam north into the San Gabriel Mountains. Facilities include an athletic field, 24 hole Frisbee golf course, an extensive network of bridle, bicycle, and hiking trails.
properties.Desc1: Located at Oak Grove Drive & Foothill Boulevard (across from La Canada High School). Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to sundown. The size of the park is 1,300 acres.

properties.NAME: Eaton Blanche Park
properties.Short_Desc: Well-developed park located in the southeast section of the City offers two lighted tennis courts, one softball diamond, one lighted basketball court, open grass area, playground equipment, picnic tables, small parking lot and a rose garden.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 5.5 acres.

properties.NAME: Eaton Blanche Park
properties.Short_Desc: Well-developed park located in the southeast section of the City offers two lighted tennis courts, one softball diamond, one lighted basketball court, open grass area, playground equipment, picnic tables, small parking lot and a rose garden.
properties.Desc1: Hours of operation are from 6:00 am to 10:00 pm. The size of the park is 5.5 acres.

properties.NAME: Garfield Park
properties.Short_Desc: Garfield Park is 7 acres of improved park, including playground equipment, 2 tennis courts (lighted), picnic areas, and groomed parkland.

properties.NAME: Huntington Library Botanical Gardens
properties.Short_Desc: The Huntington Library, Art Collections and Botanical Gardens is a collections-based educational and research institution established by Henry E. Huntington and located in San Marino, California, in the United States.

properties.NAME: Eaton Canyon Park
properties.Short_Desc: Eaton Canyon Natural Area Park and Nature Center is a natural preserve located at the base of the San Gabriel Mountains.

properties.NAME: Bailey Canyon Park
properties.Short_Desc: The Bailey Canyon Wilderness Park provides access to the Canyon View nature trail and Live Oak self-guided nature trail.
properties.Address: 451 W. Carter Ave Sierra Madre CA 91024

properties.NAME: Michillinda Park
properties.Short_Desc: This beautiful park is located within the unincorporated area of Pasadena. Families find this to be the perfect weekend getaway for picnics and afternoon walks.

properties.NAME: Hugo Reid Park
properties.Short_Desc: 3 Tennis Courts, Windsor Field Ball Diamond and Play Area
properties.Address: Michillinda Avenue and Hugo Reid Drive

properties.NAME: Charles White Park
properties.Short_Desc: This five acre park consists of a children’s play area, picnic tables, and lots of green open space.  It is located between Lincoln Avenue and Fair Oaks Avenue in beautiful Altadena.

properties.NAME: Loma Alta Park
properties.Short_Desc: This beautiful 17.33-acre park, located in the foothill community of Altadena, features something for everyone.

properties.NAME: Brookside Park Area H
properties.Short_Desc: A large, lighted multi-purpose field.

properties.NAME: Eaton Canyon Golf Course
properties.Short_Desc: This Regulation 9-hole course features narrow fairways and rolling terrain. It is located high in the foothills with mountain and valley views.
properties.Address: 1150 North Sierra Madre Villa Avenue Pasadena, CA 91107

properties.NAME: Linda Vista Park
properties.Short_Desc: The Linda Vista Park is a public park, open to everyone from 7:00 a.m. to dusk, 7 days a week.  It is located on the 1200 block of Linda Vista Avenue.  The entrance is just south of the Linda Vista Elementary School.

properties.NAME: Rose Bowl
properties.Short_Desc: The stadium is the proud home of the Tournament of Roses Football Game, UCLA Bruin Football, Americafest Fourth of July celebration, concerts, religious services, filmings and the World's Largest Flea Market (R.G. Canning).

properties.NAME: Brookside Golf Course
properties.Short_Desc: Located in the shadows of the San Gabriel Mountains adjacent to the world famous Rose Bowl

properties.NAME: Eaton Canyon Golf Course
properties.Short_Desc: This Regulation 9-hole course features narrow fairways and rolling terrain. It is located high in the foothills with mountain and valley views.
properties.Address: 1150 North Sierra Madre Villa Avenue Pasadena, CA 91107

properties.NAME: Annandale Golf Club
properties.Short_Desc: Annandale Golf Club was established in 1906.  The 6,612 yard golf course was originally designed by William Watson and Bill Bell.
properties.Address: 1 N San Rafael Ave Pasadena, CA 91105
